selfnetd complicant gateway
====

selfnetd can manage peer relation by itself, but it is much more effective to have it helped by gateway of the network.
the gateway must support the following functions:
1. list hosts
2. host change notification
3. wakeup host

selfnetd comlicant gateway needs to listen on tcp port 2300, this channel use json as its packet payload.

// out
{
    "host-list":
        [
            {
                "ip": "1.2.3.4"
                "mac": "01-02-03-04-05-06",
                "hostname": "abcd",
            },
            {
                "ip": "1.2.3.4"
                "mac": "01-02-03-04-05-06",
                "hostname": "",
            },
        ]
}

// out
{
    "host-appear":
        {
            "ip": "1.2.3.4"
            "mac": "01-02-03-04-05-06",
            "hostname": "abcd",
        },
}

// out
{
    "host-disappear": "1.2.3.4",
}

// in
{
    "command": "try-wakeup",
    "host": "abcd",
}
